jade
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:Either of two types of hard, usually green, fine-grained minerals, used as an ornamental stone or in jewellery; in New Zealand formerly, now occasionally, applied to greenstone; =greenstone.
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See: also jadeite
Pronunciation:
Notes:
